    {
      "question": "In $\\triangle ABC$, $DE \\parallel BC$ such that $AD = (4x - 3) \\text{ cm}$, $AE = (8x - 7) \\text{ cm}$, $BD = (3x - 1) \\text{ cm}$, and $CE = (5x - 3) \\text{ cm}$. Find the value of $x$.",
      "answer": "$x = 1$ or $x = 0.8$",
      "solution": {
        "steps": [
          "Apply Thales Theorem (Basic Proportionality Theorem) since $DE \\parallel BC$.",
          "Set up the ratio $\\frac{AD}{BD} = \\frac{AE}{CE}$.",
          "Solve the resulting quadratic equation for $x$."
        ],
        "derivation": "$\\frac{4x - 3}{3x - 1} = \\frac{8x - 7}{5x - 3} \\\\ (4x - 3)(5x - 3) = (8x - 7)(3x - 1) \\\\ 20x^2 - 12x - 15x + 9 = 24x^2 - 8x - 21x + 7 \\\\ 20x^2 - 27x + 9 = 24x^2 - 29x + 7 \\\\ 4x^2 - 2x - 2 = 0 \\\\ 2x^2 - x - 1 = 0 \\\\ (2x + 1)(x - 1) = 0 \\\\ x = 1, x = -0.5$"
      },
