    {
      "question": "In $\\triangle ABC$, $\\angle A = 90^\\circ$ and $AD \\perp BC$. If $AD = 8 \\text{ cm}$ and $BD = 4 \\text{ cm}$, find the length of $CD$.",
      "answer": "$16 \\text{ cm}$",
      "solution": {
        "steps": [
          "Use the property of similarity in a right triangle where the altitude to the hypotenuse divides the triangle into two triangles similar to the whole and each other.",
          "Establish the ratio $\\triangle ADB \\sim \\triangle CDA$.",
          "Solve for $CD$ using $\\frac{AD}{BD} = \\frac{CD}{AD}$."
        ],
        "derivation": "$\\text{In } \\triangle ABC, \\angle A = 90^\\circ \\text{ and } AD \\perp BC. \\\\ \\triangle ADB \\sim \\triangle CDA \\\\ \\frac{AD}{CD} = \\frac{BD}{AD} \\\\ AD^2 = BD \\times CD \\\\ 8^2 = 4 \\times CD \\\\ 64 = 4 \\times CD \\\\ CD = 16 \\text{ cm}$"
      },
