    {
      "question": "The perimeters of two similar triangles are $30 \\text{ cm}$ and $20 \\text{ cm}$ respectively. If one side of the first triangle is $9 \\text{ cm}$, find the length of the corresponding side of the second triangle.",
      "answer": "$6 \\text{ cm}$",
      "solution": {
        "steps": [
          "Recall that the ratio of perimeters of two similar triangles is equal to the ratio of their corresponding sides.",
          "Set up the proportion $\\frac{P_1}{P_2} = \\frac{S_1}{S_2}$.",
          "Substitute the given values and solve for $S_2$."
        ],
        "derivation": "$\\frac{P_1}{P_2} = \\frac{S_1}{S_2} \\\\ \\frac{30}{20} = \\frac{9}{S_2} \\\\ 30 \\times S_2 = 20 \\times 9 \\\\ 30 \\times S_2 = 180 \\\\ S_2 = \\frac{180}{30} = 6 \\text{ cm}$"
      },
