    {
      "question": "In $\\triangle ABC$, $P$ and $Q$ are points on sides $AB$ and $AC$ such that $PQ \\parallel BC$. If $AP = 3 \\text{ cm}$, $PB = 2 \\text{ cm}$ and $AQ = 2.7 \\text{ cm}$, find $AC$.",
      "answer": "$4.5 \\text{ cm}$",
      "solution": {
        "steps": [
          "Apply the Thales theorem: $\\frac{AP}{AB} = \\frac{AQ}{AC}$.",
          "Calculate $AB = AP + PB = 3 + 2 = 5 \\text{ cm}$.",
          "Solve the ratio for $AC$."
        ],
        "derivation": "$\\frac{AP}{AP + PB} = \\frac{AQ}{AC} \\\\ \\frac{3}{3 + 2} = \\frac{2.7}{AC} \\\\ \\frac{3}{5} = \\frac{2.7}{AC} \\\\ 3 \\times AC = 5 \\times 2.7 \\\\ 3 \\times AC = 13.5 \\\\ AC = 4.5 \\text{ cm}$"
      },
